DC  L-threonine degradation II
DR  MetaCyc; THREONINE-DEG2-PWY;
CC  The threonine dehydrogenase-based pathway is the primary route of
CC  L-threonine degradation in both prokaryotes and eukaryotes. Threonine
CC  dehydrogenase catalyzes the oxidation of threonine by NAD+ to
CC  L-2-amino-3-oxobutanoate. The later is converted by 2-amino-3-ketobutyrate
CC  CoA ligase into glycine and acetyl-CoA [1]. In a study of 75 soil bacteria
CC  capable of growth on L-threonine, the threonine dehydrogenase pathway was
CC  predominant, being the main route in 46 organisms [2].
